cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with optimizing cell association in a cellular network infrastructure, specifically for Device-to-Device (D2D) communications. This involves minimizing interference caused by D2D devices onto cellular communications in the uplink and improving D2D resource utilization efficiency. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely categories include cs.IT (Information Theory) as optimization techniques are used, cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper proposes an optimization framework, cs.MM (Multimedia) as the paper discusses quality of experience, and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as interference management is a security concern.
